message: Maybe you are idiot or blind, but I made you a long list of Serhiys in your page
"if everyone will change the name to the name he prefers will be a chaos." Are you dumb or an idiot??? Everywhere is Serhiy, but Kolyan77 decided that here it should be Serhii.
It is not about preferences. It is about Wikipedia consensus.

Undid revision 1181231019 by [[Special:Contributions/Kolya77|Kolya77]] ([[User talk:Kolya77|talk]]) Wikipedia consensus is Serhiy. You can bring a thousand more sources, it won't change it. If you don't agree with it, you can open a dispute on this consensus.

Undid revision 1181225345 by [[Special:Contributions/Kolya77|Kolya77]] ([[User talk:Kolya77|talk]]) Balti official page is not the ultimate source who decides the transcript. Did you check the pages I shared?

It is just a pdf from football federation. The guy who wrote it could write it Sergiy, Sergey, Serhii, Serhiy. It is not that guy could decides the transcript from Cyrillic to Latin script. Normally it is based on how a name is covered in media. Since this guy is not covered enough in media, it should according to Wikipedia consensus, which is Serhiy. Check other football personalities like: [[Serhiy Rebrov]], [[Serhiy Sydorchuk]], [[Serhiy Kryvtsov]], [[Serhiy Nazarenko]], [[Serhiy Bezhenar]].
